description.description: This dictionary contains information of all the other dictionaries with this large metadata file
description.signs: Signs is the list of all signs used within this dataset. These are the base individual words that the dataset was originally collected with
description.sign_categories:
Sign categories is the list of all categories that the model will predict on. Sign categories merges homosigns together into one category to 
    improve recognition rates. Refer to 'homosigns' for more details
description.homosigns:
Homosigns is the list of all signs deemed to be signed the same way or indistinguishable from each other in an isolated sign language context where
    the user is signing with a smartphone. Comparisons were made based on the reference videos provided by DPAN. Two signs being placed together in the homosign category
    does not imply they are the same sign, just simply that they were visually similar.
description.category_to_signs: This is a dictionary that maps categories to the group of signs composing of that category. Refer to 'sign_categories' for more details
description.sign_to_category:
This is a dictionary that maps the sign to its categorical name. This is useful if a sign is apart of a homosign group and needs to be mapped to
    its category name.
description.idx_to_sign: This is a dictionary mapping the index (of an prediction array from the output of a model) to the sign. This is useful for interpreting the output of a model.
description.sign_to_idx: This is a dictionary mapping the sign to its assigned index.
description.sign_to_phonology:
This is a dictionary mapping PopSign signs to the ASLLEX phoneme classes. Phoneme classes given are numbers associated with each phoneme class (e.g. the 'open_8' handshape
    is assigned to index := 31 (out of 42)). Refer to 'idx_to_phoneme' and 'phoneme_to_idx' for more details. Mappings were made if the exact glosses matched, but further in depth mappings will be done in the future. 
    Refer to the ASLLEX paper for more details. ASLLEX is for non-commercial use only.
description.category_to_phonology:
This is a dictionary mapping from sign categories to ASLLEX phoneme classes. Refer to 'sign_to_phonology' and 'sign_categories' for more details. 
    Category phonemes are copied over from the signs in the category. Preference is given for signs with metadata. If there are multiple signs with metadata, one is chosen arbitrarily
    since all signs in the sign category should be signed the same way.
description.idx_to_phoneme: Index to phoneme. Accessed via metadata['idx_to_phoneme']['Phoneme_parameter'][index] = value. Refer to 'sign_to_phonology' for more details.
description.phoneme_to_idx: Phoneme to index. Accessed via metadata['phoneme_to_idx']['Phoneme_parameter'][value] = idx. Refer to 'sign_to_phonology' for more details.
